R Notebook

Homework Info

Learning Objectives

  • Practice making plots with ggplot2
  • Create your own theme and use it with plots

Background

QikBit is a start-up company producing low cost fitness trackers. Their flagship product, the KwikBit Unit1 (spot the mistake on the patent form) reproduces the functionality of the best-in-class commercial fitness trackers, but is cheap to make. They are currently preparing to pitch to a potential investor and require a selection of charts to include in their presentation and promotional materials.

Data

The data for this assignment is provided in the CodeClanData package.

  • qb_revenue_breakdown
  • qb_monthly_sales
  • qb_competitors
  • qb_device_data

Take a little time before you start to familiarise yourself with the data.

library(tidyverse)
library(CodeClanData)

Attaching package: ‘CodeClanData’

The following objects are masked _by_ ‘.GlobalEnv’:

    benefits, monthly_sales, olympics_overall_medals,
    pets, students

The following object is masked from ‘package:dplyr’:

    starwars

The following object is masked from ‘package:tidyr’:

    population
revenue_breakdown <- qb_revenue_breakdown
monthly_sales <- qb_monthly_sales
competitors <- qb_competitors
device_data <- qb_device_data

Part 1

Question 1.
Take the data in the dataset qb_revenue_breakdown and make a stacked bar chart showing the sources of revenue across the two years in the dataset. 

```r
ggplot(revenue_breakdown) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product) +
  geom_col()

**Question 2.**  
Make a line chart showing monthly sales of the "flagship product" - the 'KwikBit Unit 1' - over the last year. This data is inside `qb_monthly_sales`, but you will need to use `filter()` or `subset()` (base `R)`.
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubW9udGhseV9zYWxlcyAlPiUgXG4gIGZpbHRlcihDYXNoZmxvdyA9PSBcXEt3aWtiaXQgVW5pdCAxIFNhbGVzXFwpICU+JSBcbiAgZmlsdGVyKERhdGUgPiBcXDIwMTktMDEtMDFcXCkgJT4lIFxuICBnZ3Bsb3QoKSArXG4gIGFlcyh4ID0gRGF0ZSwgeSA9IEFtb3VudCkgK1xuICBnZW9tX2xpbmUoKSArXG4gIGxhYnMoXG4gICAgdGl0bGUgPSBcXDIwMTkgc2FsZXMgZm9yIEt3aWtCaXQgVW5pdCBcXFxuICApXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
monthly_sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow == \Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales\) %>% 
  filter(Date > \2019-01-01\) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Date, y = Amount) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = \2019 sales for KwikBit Unit \
  )

**Question 3.**  
Make a line chart showing monthly revenue and costs over the last year. This data is also in `qb_monthly_sales`.                                
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxubW9udGhseV9zYWxlcyAlPiUgXG4gIGZpbHRlcihDYXNoZmxvdyAhPSBcIkt3aWtiaXQgVW5pdCAxIFNhbGVzXCIpICU+JSBcbiAgZmlsdGVyKERhdGUgPiBcIjIwMTktMDEtMDFcIikgJT4lIFxuICBnZ3Bsb3QoKSArXG4gIGFlcyh4ID0gRGF0ZSwgeSA9IEFtb3VudCwgY29sb3VyID0gQ2FzaGZsb3cpICtcbiAgZ2VvbV9saW5lKCkgK1xuICBsYWJzKFxuICAgIHRpdGxlID0gXCIyMDE5IGNvc3RzXCJcbiAgKSArXG4gIHNjYWxlX3hfZGF0ZShkYXRlX2JyZWFrcyA9IFwiMSBtb250aFwiLCBkYXRlX2xhYmVscyA9IFwiJWQtJWItJXlcIikgK1xuICB0aGVtZShheGlzLnRleHQueCA9IGVsZW1lbnRfdGV4dChhbmdsZSA9IDQ1LCBoanVzdCA9IDEpKVxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
monthly_sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow != "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales") %>% 
  filter(Date > "2019-01-01") %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Date, y = Amount, colour = Cashflow) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = "2019 costs"
  ) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "1 month", date_labels = "%d-%b-%y") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

NA
NA

Question 4.
Show annual sales of personal fitness trackers over the last 5 years broken down by company as a ribbon plot (use geom_area). This data is in qb_competitors. 

```r
competitors %>% 
  mutate(Revenue_thosands = Revenue/1000) %>% 
  ggplot()+
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue_thosands, fill = Company) +
  geom_area() +
  labs(
    y = \Revenue / 1000\
    
  )

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->



**Question 5.**  
Now show the sales from the four competitors as a line graph. Include an extra layer that shows the data points used to make the lines.
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuXG5jb21wZXRpdG9ycyAlPiUgXG4gIG11dGF0ZShSZXZlbnVlX3Rob3NhbmRzID0gUmV2ZW51ZS8xMDAwKSAlPiUgXG4gIGdncGxvdCgpK1xuICBhZXMoeCA9IFllYXIsIHkgPSBSZXZlbnVlX3Rob3NhbmRzLCBjb2xvdXIgPSBDb21wYW55KSArXG4gIGdlb21fbGluZSgpICtcbiAgZ2VvbV9wb2ludCgpICtcbiAgbGFicyhcbiAgICB5ID0gXFxSZXZlbnVlIC8gMTAwMFxcXG4gICAgXG4gIClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r

competitors %>% 
  mutate(Revenue_thosands = Revenue/1000) %>% 
  ggplot()+
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue_thosands, colour = Company) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    y = \Revenue / 1000\
    
  )

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

**Question 6.**  
Now the company wants to compare the number of steps that their device counts vs. their competitors. Make a line graph of the number of steps throughout time, and use faceting to compare between companies and people. The data for this is in `qb_device_data`.
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuXG5kZXZpY2VfZGF0YSAlPiUgXG4gIGZpbHRlcihjb3VudHMgPiAwKSAlPiUgXG4gIGdncGxvdCgpK1xuICBhZXMoeD0gaG91cnMsIHkgPSBjb3VudHMsIGNvbG91ciA9IGRldmljZSkgK1xuICBnZW9tX2xpbmUoKSArXG4gIGZhY2V0X2dyaWQoaWQgfiBkZXZpY2UpXG5cbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r

device_data %>% 
  filter(counts > 0) %>% 
  ggplot()+
  aes(x= hours, y = counts, colour = device) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(id ~ device)

Part 2

Question 1.
Take the plots that you produced in part one and now polish them by:

  1. Adding appropriate labels
  2. Changing the scales and coordinates when appropriate.
  3. Applying a unified theme, which is described below:
  • Graphs should have white backgrounds, and use colour sparingly.
  • There should be faint grid lines.
  • Font sizes should be ~12pt although titles should be slightly larger and axis labels can be slightly smaller.
  • All plots should use colours from the following company colour scheme.

Take the data in the dataset qb_revenue_breakdown and make a stacked bar chart showing the sources of revenue across the two years in the dataset. 

```r
ggplot(revenue_breakdown) +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue, fill = Product) +
  geom_col() + 
  labs(
    title = \Source of revenue by product\
  ) + 
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(\Accessories\ = \#E89FE9\,
               \Smart Watches\ = \#50434F\,
               \Subscription Services\ = \#B6A7B5\,
               \Trackers\ = \#F9A472\)
    )

2.
**Question 2.**  
Make a line chart showing monthly sales of the "flagship product" - the 'KwikBit Unit 1' - over the last year. This data is inside `qb_monthly_sales`, but you will need to use `filter()` or `subset()` (base `R)`.
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxubW9udGhseV9zYWxlcyAlPiUgXG4gIGZpbHRlcihDYXNoZmxvdyA9PSBcIkt3aWtiaXQgVW5pdCAxIFNhbGVzXCIpICU+JSBcbiAgZmlsdGVyKERhdGUgPiBcIjIwMTktMDEtMDFcIikgJT4lIFxuICBnZ3Bsb3QoKSArXG4gIGFlcyh4ID0gRGF0ZSwgeSA9IEFtb3VudCkgK1xuICBnZW9tX2xpbmUoY29sb3VyID0gXCIjRTg5RkU5XCIsIHNpemUgPSAyKSArXG4gIGxhYnMoXG4gICAgdGl0bGUgPSBcIjIwMTkgU2FsZXMgZm9yIEt3aWtCaXQgVW5pdCBcIlxuICApICtcbiAgdGhlbWVfbWluaW1hbCgpIFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
monthly_sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow == "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales") %>% 
  filter(Date > "2019-01-01") %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Date, y = Amount) +
  geom_line(colour = "#E89FE9", size = 2) +
  labs(
    title = "2019 Sales for KwikBit Unit "
  ) +
  theme_minimal() 
Warning: Using `size` aesthetic for lines was deprecated in ggplot2 3.4.0.
Please use `linewidth` instead.

NA


Question 3.
Make a line chart showing monthly revenue and costs over the last year. This data is also in qb_monthly_sales.

```r
monthly_sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow == \Cost\) %>% 
  filter(Date > \2019-01-01\) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Date, y = Amount) +
  geom_line(colour = \#E89FE9\) +
  labs(
    title = \2019 costs\
  )+
  theme_minimal()

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->


**Question 5.**  
Now show the sales from the four competitors as a line graph. Include an extra layer that shows the data points used to make the lines.
<br>


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuXG5jb21wZXRpdG9ycyAlPiVcbiAgbXV0YXRlKFJldmVudWVfdGhvc2FuZHMgPSBSZXZlbnVlIC8gMTAwMCkgJT4lXG4gIGdncGxvdCgpICtcbiAgYWVzKHggPSBZZWFyLCB5ID0gUmV2ZW51ZV90aG9zYW5kcywgY29sb3VyID0gQ29tcGFueSkgK1xuICBnZW9tX2xpbmUoKSArXG4gIGxhYnMoeSA9IFxcUmV2ZW51ZSAvIDEwMDBcXCxcbiAgICAgICB0aXRsZSA9IFxcQW5udWFsIHNhbGVzIGJ5IHllYXIgZm9yIGVhY2ggY29tcGFueVxcKSArXG4gIHNjYWxlX2NvbG9yX21hbnVhbChcbiAgICB2YWx1ZXMgPSBjKFxuICAgICAgXFxDb21wZXRpdG9yIDFcXCA9IFxcI0U4OUZFOVxcLFxuICAgICAgXFxDb21wZXRpdG9yIDJcXCA9IFxcIzUwNDM0RlxcLFxuICAgICAgXFxDb21wZXRpdG9yIDNcXCA9IFxcI0I2QTdCNVxcLFxuICAgICAgXFxDb21wZXRpdG9yIDRcXCA9IFxcI0Y5QTQ3MlxcXG4gICAgKVxuICApICtcbiAgdGhlbWVfbWluaW1hbCgpICsgXG4gIGdlb21fcG9pbnQoKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r

competitors %>%
  mutate(Revenue_thosands = Revenue / 1000) %>%
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = Year, y = Revenue_thosands, colour = Company) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(y = \Revenue / 1000\,
       title = \Annual sales by year for each company\) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      \Competitor 1\ = \#E89FE9\,
      \Competitor 2\ = \#50434F\,
      \Competitor 3\ = \#B6A7B5\,
      \Competitor 4\ = \#F9A472\
    )
  ) +
  theme_minimal() + 
  geom_point()

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

**Question 6.**  
Now the company wants to compare the number of steps that their device counts vs. their competitors. Make a line graph of the number of steps throughout time, and use faceting to compare between companies and people. The data for this is in `qb_device_data`.
<br>

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuXG5kZXZpY2VfZGF0YSA8LSBcbm11dGF0ZShkZXZpY2VfZGF0YSwgZGVjaW1hbF9ob3VyID0gaG91cnMgKyAobWlucy82MCkpXG5cblxuZGV2aWNlX2RhdGEgJT4lIFxuICBmaWx0ZXIoY291bnRzID4gMCkgJT4lIFxuICBnZ3Bsb3QoKStcbiAgYWVzKHg9IGRlY2ltYWxfaG91ciwgeSA9IGNvdW50cywgY29sb3VyID0gZGV2aWNlKSArXG4gIGdlb21fbGluZSgpICtcbiAgZmFjZXRfZ3JpZChpZCB+IGRldmljZSkgK1xuICB0aGVtZV9taW5pbWFsKCkgKyBcbiAgbGFicyh0aXRsZSA9IFwiTnVtYmVyIG9mIHN0ZXBzIGJ5IGNvdW50ZWQgYnkgY29tZXRpdG9yc1wiKSArXG4gIHNjYWxlX2NvbG9yX21hbnVhbChcbiAgICB2YWx1ZXMgPSBjKFxuICAgICAgXCJjb21wZXRpdG9yMVwiID0gXCIjRTg5RkU5XCIsXG4gICAgICBcImNvbXBldGl0b3IyXCIgPSBcIiM1MDQzNEZcIixcbiAgICAgIFwiY29tcGV0aXRvcjNcIiA9IFwiI0I2QTdCNVwiLFxuICAgICAgXCJxaWtiaXQxXCIgPSBcIiNGOUE0NzJcIlxuICAgICkpXG5cbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r

device_data <- 
mutate(device_data, decimal_hour = hours + (mins/60))


device_data %>% 
  filter(counts > 0) %>% 
  ggplot()+
  aes(x= decimal_hour, y = counts, colour = device) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(id ~ device) +
  theme_minimal() + 
  labs(title = "Number of steps by counted by cometitors") +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      "competitor1" = "#E89FE9",
      "competitor2" = "#50434F",
      "competitor3" = "#B6A7B5",
      "qikbit1" = "#F9A472"
    ))
